TEST CASE 1:

Input: 1 -> 3 -> 4 
       x = 3
Output: 1 -> 3
Explanation:
After deleting the node at 3rd
position (1-base indexing), the
linked list is as 1 -> 3. 

TEST CASE 2:

Input: 1 -> 5 -> 2 -> 9 
x = 2
Output: 1 -> 2 -> 9
Explanation: 
After deleting the node at 2nd
position (1-based indexing), the
linked list is as 1 -> 2 -> 9.
